(firstQuint)HealthCall-S: A Pilot Study Targeting Concurrent Non-injection Drug Use and Alcohol in HIV Primary Care Clinics.

 The goal of this study is to compare the effects of brief motivational interviewing with participation in HealthCall to brief motivational interviewing alone on non-injection drug and alcohol use.

 HealthCall involves 2-3 minutes of daily smartphone use to track drug use, drinking behaviors and other aspects of health, followed by personalized feedback in a graph after 30 and 60 days of using the smartphone.

